  "body": "As a developer, I want to have one place for platform-specific styles.\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug / refactor\r\n\r\nWe have two different ways of declaring platform specific styles. Some screens use `:ios`/`:android` inline in `style.cljs` (e.g. https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/883b702fcba7d94b93828ccfaa6d6053100fe52d/src/status_im/ui/screens/group/styles.cljs#L42-L48), whereas others declare styles in a global platform specific `platform.cljs` namespace (https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/src/status_im/ios/platform.cljs#L7-L66).\r\n\r\nThe former makes more sense to me in terms of locality. The latter is legacy code.\r\n\r\nProbable offenders:\r\n\r\n```\r\nOskars-MacBook-Pro:status-react oskarth$ ag component-style -l\r\nsrc/status_im/android/platform.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/chat/screen.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/chat/views/actions.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/chat/views/input/animations/expandable.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/chat/views/input/animations/responder.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/chat/views/input/utils.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/chat/views/toolbar_content.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/components/chat_icon/styles.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/components/status_bar.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/components/text_field/styles.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/components/toolbar/view.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/components/toolbar_new/styles.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ios/platform.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ui/screens/chats_list/styles.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ui/screens/contacts/new_contact/views.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ui/screens/contacts/views.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ui/screens/discover/all_dapps/views.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ui/screens/discover/components/views.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ui/screens/discover/views.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ui/screens/group/views.cljs\r\nsrc/status_im/ui/screens/profile/styles.cljs\r\n```\r\n(sans platform.cljs)",
